For example, on November 19, 2020 at 9:50 a.m., a sale order was placed in =
an account in the name of =E2=80=9CA.B.,=E2=80=9D an associate of Patten. T=
he order was placed from an IP address associated with Patten. The followin=
g week, a buy order was placed in the account of =E2=80=9CM.M.,=E2=80=9D al=
so an associate of Patten, from the same IP address associated with Patten.=
 The wash trade was immediately executed, resulting in an exchange of 200 s=
hares at a price of $10.45 per share between one Patten-controlled account =
and another Patten-controlled account.
We talk sometimes around here about US equity market structure, about spoof=
ing, about high-frequency traders who race to buy stock a millisecond ahead=
