  [1] Despite keeping labor costs extraordinarily low: It  paid $360 for la=
bor in 2018, $120 in 2019 and $126 in 2020. I don=E2=80=99t know! There has=
 been a lot of reporting about the stock market implications of the deli, a=
nd a certain amount of   reporting about its sandwiches, but I have never r=
ead anything about how it hires and retains counter workers.=20


  [2] Does? In April it merged with a private company, effectively taking t=
hat company public, and is now called Makamer Holdings Inc., but it still t=
rades, infrequently, under its old HWIN ticker.


  [3] Some of these details are from Bloomberg data, not the SEC complaint.


  [4] A more technical point is that you might want to =E2=80=9Cuplist=E2=
=80=9D the stock. US companies that are publicly traded but not listed on a=
 big exchange (Nasdaq or the New York Stock Exchange) are said to trade =E2=
=80=9Cover the counter,=E2=80=9D but there are tiers of the over-the-counte=
r markets, which are administered by OTC Markets Group Inc. =E2=80=9CThe =
=E2=80=98OTC Pink Open Market=E2=80=99 (=E2=80=98OTC Pink Market=E2=80=99) =
is the lowest tier marketplace for the trading of OTC securities,=E2=80=9D =
 says the SEC, while =E2=80=9Cthe =E2=80=98OTCQB=E2=80=99 is the middle tie=
r marketplace for the trading of OTC securities and consists mainly of earl=
y-stage and developing U.S. and international companies.=E2=80=9D Moving fr=
om the Pink Market to the OTCQB =E2=80=9Cprovided more visibility for Homet=
own International=E2=80=99s securities, fewer obstacles to trading its shar=
es, and enabled the shareholders whose shares were registered in the Form S=
-1 to sell their shares at a price higher than $6.50, as the Form S-1 Regis=
tration Statement capped the sale price at $6.50 per share until the shares=
 were quoted on certain markets, including the OTCQB.=E2=80=9D And so the S=
EC alleges that the defendants did schemes to get Hometown uplisted, includ=
ing distributing shares to their friends to meet the 50-shareholder require=
ment.=20


  [5] None of these April trades are mentioned in the SEC=E2=80=99s and DOJ=
=E2=80=99s examples of wash trades, but that doesn=E2=80=99t mean that they=
 definitively weren=E2=80=99t.


  [6] This is not unrelated to a hypothetical trade I=20
wrote about last January, where you are a hedge fund, you buy stock in a sm=
all-cap company, and then you put out a bearish-sounding note about it so r=
etail investors rush in to punish you by buying the stock, which you then s=
ell.


  [7] There were about 7.8 million Hometown shares outstanding pre-merger, =
 but =E2=80=9Cin connection with the Merger, certain pre-Merger stockholder=
s of the Company agreed to return 1,450,000 shares of the Company=E2=80=99s=
 common stock to the Company for cancellation.=E2=80=9D


  [8] Also a perfectly acceptable way to communicate with someone sitting n=
ext to you, though you *might* talk to them instead.


  [9] Fun fact: During my time at Goldman, there was a scandal about staff =
allegedly referring to customers as =E2=80=9Cmuppets,=E2=80=9D which led to=
 a firmwide search of electronic messages to catch references to muppets. I=
 am not joking. =E2=80=9CGoldman=E2=80=99s =E2=80=98muppet hunt=E2=80=99 dr=
aws a blank,=E2=80=9D was a  real Financial Times headline. One fallout of =
this is that it became very much frowned upon to swear in IMs, or even to u=
se swear abbreviations like =E2=80=9Cwtf=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cfml.=E2=80=9D=
 If you typed =E2=80=9Cwtf=E2=80=9D in an IM you=E2=80=99d get a stern talk=
ing-to from compliance.=20


  [10] Similarly, you never see prosecutors announce a murder conviction by=
 saying =E2=80=9Cthis murderer violated the very important law against murd=
er.=E2=80=9D Any time a regulator has to say explicitly that a rule is =E2=
=80=9Cvery important,=E2=80=9D that=E2=80=99s because he has some doubts.


