 year</a> and said exactly that: It was a shell company designed to take an=
 Asian private company public in the US. He explained in=C2=A0detail:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe concept of shell companies has ex=
isted globally for many years,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CThese are broadly=
 quasi-dormant public companies, that can be used to merge with private com=
panies quickly and easily.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to Jain, repurposing an existing bus=
iness for M&amp;A is an efficient way to extend the Spac model to smaller d=
eals. =E2=80=9CThe target companies we=E2=80=99re speaking to are in the $3=
00m to $600m zip code in terms of valuation,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CTo =
get it to work from a public market perspective, the Spac needs to be $75m =
to $100m.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yet setting up a Spac can cost millions of dol=
lars in administration fees alone, eating up a large portion of the value i=
n such a small deal. =E2=80=9C[Hometown] is a more flexible structure=E2=80=
=89.=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89.=E2=80=89with a longer time to find a target, and a=
 better economic uplift,=E2=80=9D Jain said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt works like a mini-Spac,=E2=80=9D h=
e added. =E2=80=9CWhen you execute the merger, the name changes, the ticker=
 changes, the board changes, the management changes, everything changes, as=
 the merged entity enters the US capital markets.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6 Jain b=
elieves that, with the right acquisition target, Hometown may be able to li=
st on the Nasdaq exchange.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again: This is the sort of thing that is often=
=C2=A0<em>accompanied=C2=A0</em>by shadiness, but it is not itself obviousl=
y illegal. Jain talked about it openly with the FT last year, and the SEC a=
nd prosecutors have nothing bad to say about <em>him</em>; he was not named=
 in this week=E2=80=99s complaints.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Instead <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/29201598.267534/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMi8wOS8y=
